00045 /// @ingroup IFORM
00046 /// Statically available information about iforms.
00047 /// Values are returned by #xed_iform_map().
00048 typedef struct XED_DLL_EXPORT  xed_iform_info_s {
00049     xed_iclass_enum_t iclass;
00050     xed_category_enum_t category;
00051     xed_extension_enum_t extension;
00052     xed_isa_set_enum_t isa_set;
00053 } xed_iform_info_t;
00054 
00055 
00056 /// @ingroup IFORM
00057 /// Map the #xed_iform_enum_t to a pointer to a #xed_iform_info_t which indicates the 
00058 /// #xed_iclass_enum_t, the #xed_category_enum_t and the #xed_extension_enum_t for the
00059 /// iform. Returns 0 if the iform is not a valid iform.
00060 XED_DLL_EXPORT const xed_iform_info_t* xed_iform_map(xed_iform_enum_t iform);
00061 
00062 /// @ingroup IFORM
00063 /// Return the maximum number of iforms for a particular iclass.  This
00064 /// function returns valid data as soon as global data is initialized. (This
00065 /// function does not require a decoded instruction as input).
00066 XED_DLL_EXPORT xed_uint32_t xed_iform_max_per_iclass(xed_iclass_enum_t iclass);
